cathodic biofuels alfred m spormann laboratory home members members of the spormann lab teaching courses offered by alfred m spormann publications spormann lab pubs contact contacting the spormann lab cathodic biofuels a new exciting research focus in our lab is to understand the molecular basis of uptake of cathodic electrons in some bacteria both as catabolic electron donor and as reductant for autotrophic co 2 fixation to produce hydrocarbons or their biosynthetic precursors this process is sometimes referred to as bioelectrosynthesis and represents a novel promising approach for microbial production of biofuels that does not involve biomass or photosynthetic microorganisms in our molecular research we are focusing on the initial reactions of direct or indirect uptake of cathodic electrons into model microorganisms as well as into novel microbial isolates in a second approach we are investigating the direct reduction of nad p by cathodic electrons for in vitro reductions reactions and reconstituted reduction pathways metabolic redox processes in biogeochemistry and bioenergy up microbial mineral and anode reduction 0 september 21 2010 lab links research redox cathodic biofuels minerals and anodes microbial biofilms h2ase chip dehalogenation gut microbes strain database group meeting bioinformatic tools protocols clark network user login login with your sunetid username password create new account request new password
